commit_list.message: Restoring node dirty calls after properties are set to trigger mutations
Removed mutation calls from sync_property_with_attrs_style method in order to avoid reparsing serialized output
Removing unnecessary field from serialization css enum
Changing update_inline_style to process multiple declarations at once to handle shorthand serialization better
Fixing python to_css codegen error
Shorthand serialization now takes iterators instead of array slice as argument
Adding more efficient way of determining if PropertyDeclaration is important
Converted serialization methods to implement the to_css trait, writing to string buffers to save string allocations for every result
Making fixes based on suggestions from nox and SimonSapin
Added test for serialize method
Added sync_property_with_attrs_style method to serialize style string when inline style is changed
Removed previously copied serialize_shorthand method as well as unnecessary calls to document.content_changed

For Shorthand impl, added to_name method and copied serialize_shorthand
from cssstyledeclaration.rs file

For PropertyDeclaration impl, added shorthands method to get the shorthands associated
with the current longhand

For PropertyDeclarationBlock impl, added serialize algorithm
Adding vscode and intellij settings folders to gitignore
Setting current color to black if canvas is not rendered in document
Adding warning to properties.mako.rs regarding the Mako parser mangling  Rust code
Changed blob to use DataSlice with Arc in order to limit wasteful copying of byte vector
Enabled use of FontFamily enum type and replaced plain string parameters with enum
Removed duplicate webdriver_traits file and added webdriver handler for GetWindowSize, IsSelected and IsEnabled
Restoring expected failures for several .ini files
Added unit tests for shorthand serialization
Adding support for correct shorthand serialization

Removed some sources of panic from script thread and devtools, using Option values instead to indicate when a pipeline context is missing where appropriate. Additionally, removed erroneous method get_browsing_context.

style(all): Minor typo/grammar fixes
